<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">The name refers to the centrally depressed, umbilicate basidiocarps, which resemble an eye or a loudspeaker; zhujian is a mythical one-eyed Chinese creature who is usually very noisy, like a walking loudspeaker.</paragraph>
