<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Q. Na, H. Zeng &amp; Y. P. Ge" authorityYear="2022" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema zhujian" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="zhujian">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema zhujian</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique among 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1951" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of its fuscous pileus with tiny, dark brown fur or scales, its distinctly radially striping with darkened lines, cheilocystidia present and pileipellis without coarse excrescences. Two species of 
<taxonomicName class="Basidiomycetes" family="Tricholomataceae" genus="Omphalina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Omphalina" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Omphalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characterized by dark pigments in the pileus- 
<taxonomicName class="Basidiomycetes" family="Tricholomataceae" genus="Omphalina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Omphalina depauperata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="depauperata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Omphalina depauperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Singer) Raithelh. and 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. subpallida" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="subpallida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">O. subpallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Singer) Raithelh., formerly named 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. subpallidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="subpallidum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. subpallidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Singer and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. depauperatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="depauperatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. depauperatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Singer, respectively, have been described from Argentina. These two species most closely resemble 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. zhujian" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="zhujian">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. zhujian</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differ in having a hyaline or white stipe, ellipsoid basidiospores, and no cheilocystidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Flora Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 84" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" refId="B56" refString="Singer, R, 1970. Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes). Flora Neotropica 3: 1 - 84, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" title="Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" volume="3" year="1970">Singer 1970</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema chrysocarpum" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="chrysocarpum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema chrysocarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. zhujian" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="zhujian">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. zhujian</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the dark brown coloration of the umbilicus of its pileus, its whitish stipe, and similarly shaped basidiospores (
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, PG" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="89 - 105" refId="B31" refString="Liu, PG, 1995. Five new species of Agaricales from Southern and Southeastern Yunnan, China. Mycotaxon 6: 89 - 105" title="Five new species of Agaricales from Southern and Southeastern Yunnan, China." volume="6" year="1995">Liu 1995</bibRefCitation>
). This taxon differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. zhujian" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="zhujian">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. zhujian</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a viscid and glabrescent pileus, pale orange lamellar margin, and pleurocystidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, PG" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="89 - 105" refId="B31" refString="Liu, PG, 1995. Five new species of Agaricales from Southern and Southeastern Yunnan, China. Mycotaxon 6: 89 - 105" title="Five new species of Agaricales from Southern and Southeastern Yunnan, China." volume="6" year="1995">Liu 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1951" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. strombodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="strombodes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. strombodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have a distinctly yellow, yellowish orange, olive yellow to yellowish brown pileus, and their micromorphological features are also different (
<bibRefCitation author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Flora Neotropica" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 84" publicationUrl="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" refId="B56" refString="Singer, R, 1970. Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes). Flora Neotropica 3: 1 - 84, http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" title="Omphalinae (Clitocybeae - Tricholomataceae, Basidiomycetes)." url="http://www.jstor.org/stable/4393664" volume="3" year="1970">Singer 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" author="Latha, KPD" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="081 - 091" refId="B30" refString="Latha, KPD, Nanu, S, Sharafudheen, SA, Manimohan, P, 2018. Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India. Phytotaxa 364 (1): 081 - 091, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" title="Two new species of Gerronema (Agaricales, Basidiomycota) from Kerala State, India." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.364.1.5" volume="364" year="2018">Latha et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
